frameDefinitions: An Agent is responsible for having intentionally performed an Act or for being the or a primary instigator behind the Act.
An Entity has ceased to exist.

A Factor affects the outcome of an Undertaking, which  can be a goal-oriented activity or the maintenance of a desirable state, the work in a Field, or something portrayed as affecting an Interested_party.
An Agent behaves as if they were a particular individual or type of Simulated_entity with the intent of misleading observers of their behavior.
An Event with multiple Participants takes place.
Under some Condition, usually left implicit, a Responsible_party is required to perform some Duty.
frameExamples: It has been determined that a relatively unknown terrorist group is <t>responsible</t> for the recent attacks.
Temperature is the most <t>critical</t> factor in successful storage.
The belfast bank robbers <t>posed</t> as police.
MATAC looks forward to your <t>participation</t> in helping promote telework in the Mid-Atlantic region.
It is my <t>duty</t> to fight any attack on the Brotherhood .
